      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-claim",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for Class II CPB device",
      "description": "The CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is credible for identifying the worst-case hemolysis operating condition across the five specified flow-speed combinations under CPB conditions. The relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by the model satisfies RH < 1 with respect to the predicate device benchmark, supporting the regulatory submission acceptance criterion. This claim is scoped to Model Risk Level 2 and is bounded by the geometric and operating envelope defined in the COU.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory decision that CFD-predicted hemolysis results are sufficient to characterize device risk without additional in-vivo testing for tolerance variation studies.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry; 5 flow-speed operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM through 7.0 L/min at 3500 RPM); Class II CPB indication; MRL 2."
    }
  ],
