      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric M) computed with uncertainty bounds; agreement within 15% for NIH.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error for NIH across 5 operating points: 8.3%. Experimental uncertainty (±12% for NIH from FDA dataset) and numerical uncertainty (GCI-based, ±1.2%) combined in quadrature. Validation metric M = 0.91, exceeding MRL 2 threshold of 0.80."
